verses.roman:
hena-kāle tumi-saba kolāhala kailā
tāhāṅ haite dhari' more ihāṅ lañā āilā

synonyms: hena-kāle—at this time; tumi-saba—all of you; kolāhala kailā—made a tumultuous sound; tāhāṅ haite—from there; dhari'-catching; more—Me; ihāṅ—here; lañā āilā—you have brought.
translation: "Just then, all of you made a tumultuous sound and carried Me from there to this place.
